'''KANT''' is a [[computer algebra system]] for mathematicians interested in [[algebraic number theory]], performing sophisticated computations in [[algebraic number field]]s, in [[global function field]]s, and in [[local field]]s.  '''KASH''' is the associated command line interface.  They have been developed by the Algebra and Number Theory research group of the Institute of Mathematics at [[Technische Universität Berlin]] under the project leadership of Prof. Dr [[Michael Pohst]]. Kant is free for non-commercial use.<ref>http://page.math.tu-berlin.de/~kant/copyright.html</ref>

